Hi,

I have a mixin looking like this:
```
import Scrollbar from 'smooth-scrollbar'

export default {
	data() {
		return {
			smooth: null
		}
	},
	mounted() {
		if (!this.$device.isMobileOrTablet && process.browser) {
			this.smooth = Scrollbar.init(this.$el.querySelector('.js-smooth'))
		}
	},
	beforeDestroy() {
		if (!this.$device.isMobileOrTablet && process.browser) {
			this.smooth.destroy() /* This one gives a null error */
		}		
	}
}
```
My problem is that `this.smooth.destroy()` returns null, because before that one is called, the next page that uses the same mixin has already overwritten this.smooth as null? Is there any way to avoid this? I didn't realise data was shared between the pages?

This only happens using the default transition mode. If I change transition mode to "out-in" it works, and I guess thats because the mixin call is delayed for the next page until the current page has been removed.

